Study

Taint (on node) repels pods; Toleration (on pod) allows it to land.
Effects: NoSchedule, PreferNoSchedule, NoExecute.
nodeSelector (simple) vs nodeAffinity (expressive: required/preferred).
Pod affinity / anti-affinity for co-location/spread.
Hands-On
kubectl taint nodes <node> gpu=true:NoSchedule
# Pod with toleration:
tolerations:
- key: gpu
  operator: Equal
  value: "true"
  effect: NoSchedule
nodeAffinity:
  requiredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
    nodeSelectorTerms:
    - matchExpressions:
      - {key: disktype, operator: In, values: [ssd]}

